news.title: SIT arrests city survey officer and clerk for tampering land records in Goregaon, Mumbai
news.para: According to the probe, eight original graphs in the city survey office showed fake constructions as on Dec 31, 2019, with Wable issuing duplicate copies of these maps, which bore the Goregaon municipal land survey officer's signature.

news.title: Prayagraj civic body appeals house owners to pay their house, water tax dues by March 31
news.para: To make the tax payment process easier, Dwivedi also announced that the Municipal Corporation and Jal Kal Department have launched a unified website,  where citizens can view their property tax and water tax details and make payments online.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government to transfer Rs 112 crore funds to 40 municipalities for developmental works
news.para: Municipal administration minister P Narayana said the govt is taking measures to strengthen the financial base of urban local bodies to take up various developmental works.

news.title: Bhubaneswar's metro rail corridor likely to extended to Cuttack: Odisha Housing Minister
news.para: "A high-level technical team on the job is evaluating the possible modification/extension of routes and design. There is no point stopping the metro just on the outskirts of Cuttack and not covering it.

news.title: Jaipur's metro line II construction to begin in mid-2025
news.para: Officials from urban development and housing (UDH) department have indicated that the state govt has demonstrated interest in laying the foundation stone, considering the forthcoming civic polls in Nov.

news.title: Chandshi residents in Nashik urge NMRDA for small plots in development plan
news.para: Central govt is providing funds for the town planning scheme in areas adjoining the cities. As a part of the same, the NMRDA will be developing the Chandshi village.

news.title: Pune: residents want redevelopment near Shaniwarwada
news.para: In 1998, a notification was issued prohibiting development within 100m of the Shaniwarwada monument. The implementation started in 2003. Local residents said development has been stuck for two decades in the area.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Thanal housing project delayed due to technical sanction
news.para: Uralungal Labour Construction Cooperative Society (ULCCS), which was awarded the construction contract last year, submitted the project estimate to corporation two months ago.

news.title: Bhojpur DM takes action against several surveyors for negligence in PMAY implementation
news.para: Besides them, the Bhojpur DM has ordered 25% curtailment in the basic pay of Shailendra Kumar, the surveyor of Shahpur block's Parsaunda panchayat, and its rural awas sahayak for the next three years.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government sets May 15 launch date for Noida airport
news.para: The directive was issued on March 10 during a review meeting with all stakeholders where chief minister Yogi Adityanath expressed unhappiness over delay in the airport's construction work, particularly the terminal building.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Construction of Space Park likely to begin in May
news.para: CEO of K-Space Park G Levin told TOI that the lowest bidder will be selected from the financial bids. We will mostly finalize the bidder in Jan last week. The work order is expected to be issued in April," he said.

news.title: Brookfield Corp sells 5.13% unit holding in BIRET for Rs 883 crore
news.para: According to the bulk deal data on the BSE, Brookfield through its two affiliates -- BSREP India Office Holdings Pte and BSREP India Office Holdings IV Pte, part of the sponsor group of BIRET -- sold nearly 3.12 crore units or 5.13 per cent unit holding in Mumbai-based REIT.

news.title: NSE plans to convert HQ into captive data center, secures land for new office in Mumbai
news.para: The National Stock Exchange (NSE) is converting its headquarters in Mumbai's Bandra-Kurla Complex (BKC) into a large data center. It will relocate to a newly allotted site in G Block. The new office, which will consolidate all operations, is expected to be completed in about three years.

news.title: NBCC Green View’s three towers set for demolition in Gurugram
news.para: The approval was issued following a request by NBCC (India) Ltd., which had submitted a representation on Jan 22. NBCC had sought permission to demolish these three towers on priority, as several balconies of Tower F had collapsed in 2024, posing a serious threat to a school adjacent to the complex.

news.title: NGT seeks report as Haryana & Rajasthan fail to raze buildings constructed in Aravalis
news.para: The tribunal directed the states to set up a monitoring committee and conduct periodic reviews to remove illegal constructions from protected Aravali land in Gurgaon, Faridabad, Nuh (Haryana) and Alwar (Rajasthan), classified as "gair mumkin pahar (uncultivable hill)".

news.title: Ghaziabad development body areas to expand, board gives nod to take over 77 villages
news.para: The GDA board, which met in Meerut on Tuesday, approved the proposal to assimilate these revenue villages. The integration process will start once UP govt ratifies the plan.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body amendment bill to slash completion certificate fee to 0.1%
news.para: The bill seeks to slash the fee for obtaining a completion certificate from up to 1% of the guidance value of a vacant site to just 0.1%.

news.title: Deadline just two weeks away, 788 lifts registered in Noida so far, 20 in Ghaziabad
news.para: The first one was held on Feb 18 in Sector 62, where over 70 RWA representatives from nearby localities attended, while the second one was on Feb 23 in Sector 77, where representatives of over 25 AOAs from Sector 50 and 7x sectors participated.

news.title: Retired judge to lead probe into illegal constructions in Mumbai: Maharashtra minister
news.para: Samant was responding to a calling attention motion raised by member Sachin Ahir, who flagged the growing menace of illegal constructions in Mumbai. Ahir sought details of action taken against illegal structures in D, E, G-South, H-West, P-North, P-South, and L wards.

news.title: CBI must investigate builder-bank nexus: Supreme Court
news.para: The Supreme Court has called for a CBI probe into the alleged builder-bank nexus causing distress to homebuyers due to delayed projects. SC wants a detailed proposal from the agency to investigate, stressing the need for quick and effective measures to address the issue.
